odal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nig1704364645122.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nig1704364645122.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nig1704364645122.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"krm1665702837406\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Intermodel Relationships\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The names of modeled entities have the format <var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity.Model</var>, in which the suffix after the dot is the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Model Name</span> property. This is a mandatory property that defines a namespace for entity. All entities with the same model name are said to be part of the same application model.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"krm1665702837406__p_d10316e1_d10317e1_d10318e1\">Inter-model relationships can exist between entities in different application models. Inter-model relationships behave as though they are owned by the Many entity. This means that when you carry out an operation on the Many entity, this also directly affects the inter-model relationship.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"krm1665702837406__p_d10319e1_d10320e1_d10321e1\">You cannot delete the One-entity for which an inter-model relationship exists. To delete the relationship, delete the Many entity.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"krm1665702837406__p_d10322e1_d10323e1_d10324e1\">When creating inter-model relationships:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"krm1665702837406__li_d4706e1_d4707e1_d4708e1\">Define inter-model relationships only when referential integrity is handled by Uniface. You cannot use the Create Script utility for inter-model relationships.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"krm1665702837406__li_d4709e1_d4710e1_d4711e1\">Limit the number of inter-model relationships.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"krm1665702837406__p_d10325e1_d10326e1_d10327e1\">If you export or import modeled entities involved in an inter-model relationship, ensure that both sides of the relationship are included. If not, the resulting relationship will be incomplete.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fnf1665702703926.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Referential Integrity</a><p>Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5755098\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5755098\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Intermodel Relationships Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Intermodel Relationships The names of modeled entities have the format Entity.Model , in which the suffix after the dot is the Model Name property. This is a mandatory property that defines a namespace for entity. All entities with the same model name are said to be part of the same application model. Inter-model relationships can exist between entities in different application models. Inter-model relationships behave as though they are owned by the Many entity. This means that when you carry out an operation on the Many entity, this also directly affects the inter-model relationship. You cannot delete the One-entity for which an inter-model relationship exists. To delete the relationship, delete the Many entity. When creating inter-model relationships: Define inter-model relationships only when referential integrity is handled by Uniface. You cannot use the Create Script utility for inter-model relationships. Limit the number of inter-model relationships. If you export or import modeled entities involved in an inter-model relationship, ensure that both sides of the relationship are included. If not, the resulting relationship will be incomplete. Related Links Referential Integrity Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}